---
import ApiLayout from "../../layouts/ApiLayout.astro";
import { apiNavigation, apiSourceUrls } from "../../lib/api.js";

const toc = [
  { id: "entry-points", text: "Primary entry points", depth: 2 },
  { id: "shape-of-the-library", text: "Shape of the library", depth: 2 },
  { id: "where-to-start", text: "Where to start", depth: 2 },
];
---

<ApiLayout
  title="API Overview"
  description="The public API surface exported by causal-order today."
  sourceUrl={apiSourceUrls.overview}
  toc={toc}
  navigation={apiNavigation}
  currentPath="/api/"
>
  <p>
    The package currently exports one public surface from <code>src/index.ts</code>. The API is
    grouped around event ordering, streaming, validation, causality comparison, clocks, anomalies,
    and types.
  </p>

  <h2 id="entry-points">Primary entry points</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/api/order-events/"><code>orderEvents()</code></a> for bounded batch ordering.</li>
    <li><a href="/api/order-event-stream/"><code>orderEventStream()</code></a> for async streaming output.</li>
    <li><a href="/api/validate-event/"><code>validateEvent()</code></a> for event-envelope validation.</li>
    <li><a href="/api/compare-by-causality/"><code>compareByCausality()</code></a> for pairwise causal comparison.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="shape-of-the-library">Shape of the library</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Types</strong>: event envelopes, ordered events, confidence, anomalies, stream batches,
      and options.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Clock helpers</strong>: HLC creation, parse, and serialize functions.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Comparison helpers</strong>: HLC comparison, causality comparison, and deterministic tie breaking.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Ordering</strong>: batch ordering, streaming ordering, tie breakers, and watermark strategies.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <pre><code>{`import {
  orderEvents,
  orderEventStream,
  validateEvent,
  compareByCausality,
} from "causal-order"`}</code></pre>

  <h2 id="where-to-start">Where to start</h2>
  <p>
    If you are using the package for the first time, start with <code>orderEvents()</code> for
    bounded replay or audit slices. Move to <code>orderEventStream()</code> when you need watermark,
    late-arrival, and correction-capable behavior.
  </p>
</ApiLayout>
